    {
      "id": "51f527c7-8593-4777-b221-9303cb790f26",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $f : \\R \\to \\R$ convexe dérivable.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f : \\R \\to \\R\\)</span> convexe dérivable.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "5f745852-016e-4030-8b50-bf349707c0c2",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $p = \\lim_{x\\to+\\infty} (f(x) - xf'(x))$ existe.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(p = \\lim_{x\\to+\\infty} (f(x) - xf&#39;(x))\\)</span> existe.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "933417c8-a52c-4737-b076-4f9b3cb43f6b",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Fonction décroissante sur $\\R^+$.",
        "html": "<p>Fonction décroissante sur <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\R^+\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "9afef638-2926-4968-866b-241159ed60ca",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On suppose $p$ fini. En utilisant le fait que $f(x) - xf'(x)$ est\n    bornée au voisinage de $+\\infty$, montrer que $\\frac{f(x)}x$ et $f'(x)$\n    admettent une même limite $m$ finie en $+\\infty$.",
        "html": "<p>On suppose <span class=\"math inline\">\\(p\\)</span> fini. En utilisant le fait que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x) - xf&#39;(x)\\)</span> est bornée au voisinage de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(+\\infty\\)</span>, montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{f(x)}x\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f&#39;(x)\\)</span> admettent une même limite <span class=\"math inline\">\\(m\\)</span> finie en <span class=\"math inline\">\\(+\\infty\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "d8fbef38-afc8-4393-a2d3-15bfc08ad15f",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$f(x) - xf'(x) = -x^2\\frac {d}{d x}\\left(\\frac {f(x)}x\\right)$.\n    Donc, $x \\mapsto \\frac {f(x) - p}x \\searrow$ et\n          $x \\mapsto \\frac {f(x) - f(0)}x \\nearrow$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x) - xf&#39;(x) = -x^2\\frac {d}{d x}\\left(\\frac {f(x)}x\\right)\\)</span>. Donc, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x \\mapsto \\frac {f(x) - p}x \\searrow\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x \\mapsto \\frac {f(x) - f(0)}x \\nearrow\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "14b4f918-aca8-422a-8882-f63cc19142e9",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer alors que $f(x) - mx - p \\to 0$ lorsque $x\\to {+\\infty}$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer alors que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x) - mx - p \\to 0\\)</span> lorsque <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x\\to {+\\infty}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "248a27a1-1801-4830-a195-eca90dd16d57",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$p\\le f(x) - mx \\le f(x) - xf'(x)$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(p\\le f(x) - mx \\le f(x) - xf&#39;(x)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ]
